                        "description": "<p>We collected <em>Takydromus</em> lizards from 3 places in China. From late April to early May of 2014, we captured 22 adult <strong><em>T. sexlineatus</em></strong> from Zhaoqing (22\u00b053\u2019 N, 112\u00b036\u2019 E) in Guangdong province, 45 adult <strong><em>T. septentrionalis</em></strong> from Wenzhou (28\u00b036\u2019 N, 119\u00b037\u2019 E) in Zhejiang provinces and 28 adult <strong><em>T. wolteri</em></strong> from Chuzhou (32\u00b017\u2019 N, 118\u00b017\u2019 E) in Anhui province. We captured adult lizards by noose or hands, and transferred lizards to the laboratory in Beijing. The thermal acclimation lasted more than 40 days (6th May to 16th June). Lizards in the <strong>warm</strong> treatment were kept in terraria in a 26 \u00b0C room with 10 h supplementary heating by 50 W UVA + UVB lamp (Qupa, Shanghai, China) per day (08:00 to 18:00), while lizards in the <strong>cold</strong> treatment were kept in terraria at 16 \u00b0C with 6 h supplementary heating per day (10:00 to 16:00). After thermal acclimation, the livers of 6 individuals under <strong>cold</strong> and <strong>warm</strong> treatments from each species were collected freshly and used for metabolite extraction. Metabolite analysis was conducted by OE Biotech (Shanghai, China) in relative quantitation.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
