                        "name": "Extraction",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Extraction",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>The livers were extracted by adding 0.48 mL extraction liquid (methanol:chloroform, 3:1, v/v) and 24 \u03bcL L-2-Chlorophenylalanine (1 mg/mL in dH2O) as internal standard. Samples were vortex mixed for 30 s, homogenized in ball mill for 4 min at 45 Hz, then ultrasound treated for 5 min (incubated in ice water). The homogenate was then centrifuged for 15 min at 13,000 rpm, 4 \u2103. The supernatant (0.4 mL) was transferred to a 2 mL GC-MS vial. Next 11 \u03bcL supernatant from each sample were pooled as the QC sample. Then the samples were dried in a vacuum concentrator without heating. The dried sample were then incubated for 30 min at 80 \u2103 after adding 80 \u03bcL of Methoxy amination hydrochloride (20 mg/mL in pyridine). Each sample was further incubated for 1.5 h at 70 \u2103 after adding 100 \u03bcL of the BSTFA regent (1 % TMCS). After cooling to the room temperature, 10 \u03bcL FAMEs (Standard mixture of fatty acid methyl esters, C8-C16: 1 mg/mL, C18-C24: 0.5 mg/mL, in chloroform) was added, and then GC-TOF-MS analysis conducted.</p>",
